chunk_content: However, in MER 2.0 the PEPFAR indicator for 202 PMTCT_ART has been simplified to collect information only at antenatal care (ANC) sites to better align with 2016 WHO Consolidated ARV guidelines, reduce burden on data collection, and improve data quality. Therefore, in reporting this indicator PEPFAR operating units should (1) utilize the H O national system whether it is able avoid double counting or not and are not expected to collect or S report this information through a separate system (2) if it this is not possible to report individuals T from both ANC and L&D, please include an explanation in the narrative whether the data is from ANC, C L&D and/or both. O U Pregnant women’s HIV status should be counted only once per pregnancy. This may be difficult if N national guidelines recommend testing a pregnant woman more than once during a pregnancy or if a T R woman seroconverts during her pregnancy and has multiple tests.
